name: labgeek/dd2vmdk
description: dd2vmdk is a *nix-based program that allows you to mount raw disk images (create d by dd, dcfldd, dc3dd, ftk imager, etc) by taking the  raw image, analyzing the master boot record (physical sector 0), and getting sp ecific information that is need to create a vmdk file.  Version 0.1 has the ability to extract data from the master boot record of any  raw image, extracted information such as heads  cylinders, sectors per track, etc. and create a working vmdk file (monolithic flat disk).
